##Confirmed cases of zero growth for 2 consecutive days, the resumption of work in Shanghai how to fight the epidemic?

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

* On 18 and 19 May, the number of newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia in Shanghai rose to zero for the second consecutive day. For this mega city of more than 24 million, the news is encouraging.
* To help the grass-roots accurate location focus on the investigation of the crowd, Shanghai into the full data collection is an important first step.
* The first day of the sea back to work, prevention and control upgrade, the city began to implement closed management of residential areas. Outside Hubei, 14 key areas of concern were identified.
* Shanghai's new pneumonia public service platform has been launched, enabling citizens to quickly register health information and access services related to epidemic prevention and control.
* In the process of closed management, neighborhood mutual supervision, group prevention and crowd control also played a great role.

On February 18 and 19, the number of newly diagnosed cases of pneumonia in Shanghai rose zero for the second day in a row. For this mega city of more than 24 million, the news is encouraging.

To help the grass-roots accurate location focus on the investigation of the crowd, into Shanghai personnel full data collection is an important first step.

The first day of Shanghai's resumption of work, prevention and control upgrade, the city began to implement closed management of residential areas. Outside Hubei, 14 key areas of concern were identified.

"Shanghai new pneumonia public service platform" officially launched, the public can quickly register health information, access to epidemic prevention and control related services. But to do a good job of prevention and control, we still need to rely on grassroots and community.

In the process of closed management, neighborhood mutual supervision, group prevention and crowd control also played a great role.

In places that need to line up, residents put on face masks and queue up consciously at a distance of about one meter, which is probably a special product of the epidemic in Shanghai.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Shortly before 1:30 p.m. on Feb. 17, Wu donned a face mask and went out with a number in line. This is the second supply of face masks in Shanghai. Each family can buy 5 face masks. "It's like handing out food stamps to buy rice. "

On that day, Wu bought five disposable masks in separate packages, costing 8 yuan, compared with 2.3 yuan for the last batch, which was sold in bulk. Each batch of masks comes from a different manufacturer, the pharmacy explained.

For the work of the residential community, Wu is still quite satisfied, although not perfect, but also feel that a special period, we need to overcome. "when an outbreak occurs, the community is the most important place. If there is chaos, it starts here. "

Wu's concerns can also be said to be a consensus among Shanghai residents. But for now, things are looking up.

As of 24:00 on February 18, for the first time in China, the number of discharged patients was higher than the number of newly diagnosed patients. Another piece of good news is that there has been no increase in new cases in eight provinces and cities, including Shanghai, Guizhou and Hainan. On February 19th no new cases were confirmed in Shanghai. For this megacity of more than 24 million people, the news of zero growth is encouraging, "Zero yesterday and zero this morning, that's great, " many citizens wrote in a post on the official wechat account, "Shanghai Post. Still, don't let your guard down. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
CARTOGRAPHY: Wu Yiting

So, Shanghai's resumption of work epidemic prevention war is how to fight?

Let's widen the focus

In Wujing town of Minhang district, Tao Miao Miao, who returned to Shanghai after the Spring Festival, could not go out to buy masks. Currently, seven members of a family from Fuyang, Anhui Province, to Shanghai in a two-bedroom home need to be isolated together for 14 days before medical isolation can be lifted if there are no symptoms.

Tao's mother, sister and two relatives of her husband were among the seven members of Miao Miao's family who drove back to Shanghai on the evening of Feb. 8 from her hometown in Fuyang, Anhui Province. The day before the relatives, who live in rented apartments in the Jiading District district of Shanghai and plan to return to the city, they received a phone call from their landlord and the head of their respective village committee, reminding them that the standards for checking at street crossings in the Jiading District district had been upgraded and that tenants would be persuaded to return. Considering that going back to Shanghai sooner or later would require a 14 day medical isolation, they decided to return to their home in Wujing town, Minhang district, with Miao Miao's family.

Back to Shanghai on the second day early in the morning, Tao Miao to the neighborhood registration back to Shanghai information, and then began home isolation. On that day, there were seven new confirmed cases and 125 confirmed cases in Tao's hometown of Fuyang, Anhui Province. Anhui has become a major disaster area outside Hubei, next to Guangdong, Henan and Zhejiang. Fuyang is the third-largest province in terms of confirmed cases, behind Hefei and Bengbu.

February 10, the first day of the resumption of work in Shanghai, prevention and control upgrade, the city began to implement closed management of residential areas. Outside of Hubei, 14 areas of focus have been identified, including Fuyang.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This for the grass-roots level, it is equivalent to an increase in the screening of the workload. On the same day, the Wujing Town Community Health Service Center received a notice on the management and control of people coming (returning) to Shanghai. The work of door-to-door investigation has increased the requirement that people from 14 key areas come to Shanghai to sign the "home isolation requirement. ".

On February 12, a three-person team made up of doctors from the Community Health Service Center, police officers from the Wujing town police station and residents'committee cadres knocked on Tao's door, asking about the process of coming to Shanghai and which service areas they passed through, have been to the focus of the epidemic areas, and took the temperature of seven people, seven people signed the "commitment to home isolation and observation. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
If all goes well, the quarantine will be lifted this Sunday, Miao Miao told NEWS8. During the period of isolation, buying vegetables and taking out the garbage are all done by the neighborhood committee. On the shopping platform, after the dishes are delivered to the gate of the community, Miao Miao will inform the staff of the Neighborhood Committee in the Wechat Group, and then the staff will send the short shuttle to the door; the daily garbage is placed at the gate before 10 o'clock every morning, there will be the staff of the Neighborhood Committee to take it away and throw it away. As for the family's home life, Miao Miao was not bored. "The men play video games, the women take the children and sleep on the floor at night. "

For Home Segregation, Miao Miao agreed, "our whole family registered in the neighborhood, began to consciously at home isolation. Hard is the neighborhood committee people. "

More than 70 people, mostly people like Miao Miao, returned to Shanghai from 14 key regions, had to be screened by a three person team of doctors, police and residents from the Community Health Service Center in Wujing town on Thursday. The list of more than 70 people was compiled from information registered on the health cloud APP by people in Shanghai, public security big data and data reported by the community.

Three-person Group A total of seven groups, according to the sub-district, each group about a dozen people home survey. At 8:30 in the morning, seven police cars set off from the Community Health Service Center. Each car had a police officer and a doctor on it. When they arrived at a community, the police officers and doctors first joined the cadres of the neighborhood committee concerned in the community, three people together according to the list of door-to-door investigation, need to find out how to return to Shanghai route, arrival time, close contact with the crowd.

In the three-person group, each role plays a different role: the police can contact the local police station to provide public security information support when they can not contact the investigating officers, doctors can be responsible for understanding the physical condition of the target, detailed inquiry contact history, Neighborhood Committee cadres more familiar with the neighborhood environment and the situation of the community personnel, can help improve the efficiency of the investigation. Once the need for isolation, the neighborhood committee cadres can also provide better follow-up isolation services.

In the process of checking out the residential area, the full set of protective clothing of the police and doctors can always attract the attention of the residents, who will wonder what happened and whether there are confirmed patients, there were even reports of suspicious persons and situations in the neighbourhood to the investigating police and doctors.

"We must explain clearly to the residents, otherwise it may be another 110 police case in the next few days, and this will be a waste of police resources. " Every time the police officer, Sun Xiaoliang, encounters a problem, he will tell the residents truthfully that this is only a key investigation, not a confirmed diagnosis, and there is no need to worry. Residents will also be placated by the neighborhood committee cadres, "if there are confirmed patients, will not come so few people. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Neighborhood Committee cadre also told the eight-point Health News, to promote epidemic prevention work, mainly in the migrant population and the local elderly in the old community is relatively difficult. In the early days, there were some residents who did not cooperate with wearing masks, but now they need passes to enter and exit the community and need to take body temperature. Some residents have not formed the habit of standing in line to take body temperature. What the residents'committee can do, however, is to constantly exhort. "For example, some elderly people who are keen to get together and bask in the Sun will be reminded to wear masks and if they must bask together, at least sit open. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"information warfare. "

The experience of returning to Shanghai from his hometown in Hunan made Xiao Tan's memory deep.

At 6:30 pm on February 10, Xiao Tan arrived at the Hemerocallis Fulva airport, clutching an N95 mask. There are two or three workers at the door wearing masks and protective clothing to take their temperature. Usually at this point of the airport, check-in, check-in window will be a long queue, the emergency channel there will always be some almost delayed passengers.

This was not the case on this day. Very few passengers. Looking around, everyone kept their heads down and wore masks, trying not to talk. Someone's wearing a blue disposable mask, someone's wearing an N95.

The flight to Shanghai was supposed to leave at 9:30. Before take-off, need to scan code to login health cloud, fill in flight information, departure location, there is no Hubei stay, residence history. After filling in the form, Tan received a message on her mobile phone: "Your Health Information Registration form has been received" , and also received the landing exit prompt: non-hubei region, no Hubei stay history passengers, from Channel B, with a Verification Code attached.

The flight did not take off until nearly 11 pm due to the Shanghai Hongqiao International Airport's outbreak control. The plane was not fully occupied. It was divided into the front, middle and rear sections, each separated by a number of empty seats.

Arriving at Hongqiao Airport, it was after midnight. Exits A, B two channels, are standing in protective clothing, wearing masks staff guarding. Non-priority areas of Xiao Tan from channel B, including the process of temperature, as well as the staff to show the phone received the Verification Code.

Xiao Tan took a taxi home to Shanghai, and the dialogue of the taxi driver let her feel the concerns of the local people, "you come back to work at home, why hurry back to Shanghai? "

Her community has a total of three entrances, back to Shanghai that night, has been closed management, Xiao Tan had to enter from the only open south gate. Before entering the community, was asked to take a temperature again, fill in back to Shanghai information. Since then, the same back to Shanghai information, from Shanghai information, physical condition, Xiao Tan was asked to do at least three times, respectively from the property, the neighborhood and the working street.

To help the grass-roots to accurately locate the focus of the investigation of the crowd, to achieve fine management, into the Shanghai People's full data collection is an important first step.

The Platform Xiao Tan filled out before taking off was developed in the current outbreak. On January 31, Shanghai new pneumonia public service platform, based on the Shanghai health cloud system, was launched, the platform carries functions such as "health dynamic observation system for people coming to Shanghai" , "online consultation platform for fever symptoms" , "real-time notification of Epidemic Situation" , "one-click investigation of fever outpatient clinic" , "appointment registration as scheduled" , etc. , members of the public can quickly register health information, access to epidemic prevention and control related services and real-time information.

An enterprise executive who took part in the platform's construction told eight-point Jianwen that the launch of the platform did not happen overnight, mainly relying on the previous data of various departments in the city to get through, this is primarily in the health of the cloud platform before the development of a sudden outbreak of the sector.

As a participant in the building of a healthy cloud system, the executive recalled that during the SARS era, the government wants to be able to have a scene like this: "a person comes to the pass, goes somewhere, the community immediately knows. ". And this time, it's done. Information-based approach to replace the original form of the statistics at hand, the road to Shanghai personnel information can be quickly implemented to the specific responsible person."

Xie Hua, director of the Shanghai Municipal Health Information Center, described to the media how information is collected and then distributed to the grass roots: After the information is collected by the municipal platform, it is distributed to the district where it is located according to the place of residence, district leaders are assigned to community health service centers, which in turn are assigned to individual staff members who are supervised. The regulations include home quarantine and two daily temperature readings.

In the prevention and control of epidemic situation, in response to urban emergencies, the information-based cooperation, so that Shanghai epidemic prevention work front-line staff have a new helper, to help the city operators to achieve a closed-loop epidemic prevention and control management. As of February 15, filling data by comparison confirmed 8 people, suspected 44 people, excluded 126 people, discharged 1 person.

The data collected through big data analysis and comparison can help decision makers understand the dynamics of the epidemic situation, and even further make the decision-making and deployment of prevention and control. "For example, the specific factory can be returned to work, which can be based on data analysis, including whether the factory employees from the focus areas, the relevant supply chain, and so on, " the executive said.

PEOPLE'S WAR

The Neighborhood Committee cadre told Eight o'clock Jianwen that most people who live in isolation at home are still very conscious. On the one hand, they have a sense of isolation. On the other hand, neighbors also play a supervisory role.

Liu Ping, a first-level inspector at the Shanghai Municipal Bureau of Justice, said that closed management is not an isolation or a blockade, but an effective and controllable control measure. The aim is to bring into play the power of community groups to prevent and control the masses and strengthen control at the source, secure the security doors in the neighborhood.

On that day, Sun's three-person team groped a total of 11 people, because there were seven members of one family. In fact, there were only five families in total, but it was already 11:30 pm when the investigation ended, which took three hours. Every time we go to a residential area, the police and doctors are already familiar with the location of the residential area residents'committee. The residents'committee cadres also know that every day there may be visits and investigations, and there will be special people on duty at the residents'committee, so find the Neighborhood Committee and the three-person Group to meet the process is very smooth, and do not delay time. The delay is mainly due to some special circumstances, the main situations encountered on this day are: the person to be checked has returned to work and is not at home; the registered housing information is actually occupied by the tenant, also need to contact me through the police station's public security information.

In Sun Xiaoliang's view, the list of big data production is just a foundation, the door-to-door investigation process needs more detailed investigation, to find out the chain of evidence. "For example, our data may only record the vehicle owner's information, so when we go to the door, we still need to ask the colleague's situation. "

In order to prevent people returning to Shanghai from concealing information, Sun Xiaoliang will ask people returning to Shanghai to provide evidence that can prove the route and time of returning to Shanghai, the evidence includes high-speed train tickets or ticket purchase information, service area consumption records, navigation software tracks and SMS alerts from telecommunications providers. "during the Spring Festival, expressways may be toll-free. We can not determine when the self-drive will arrive in Shanghai. That can also provide a record of spending after returning to Shanghai. If none of this is the case, the quarantine date for those returning to Shanghai from key areas can only begin on the day of the house-to-house inspection."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The target of Investigation shall present the evidence of short message of arrival time to the police

With the resumption of work in Shanghai, the arrival of the return peak, Sun Xiaoliang obviously feel the task of home investigation intensified. "On February 9, the day before the resumption of work, a total of more than 300 people visited Wujing town. "

In Shanghai, the epidemic prevention and control measures were summarized as "four-pronged approach" -- medical treatment, control at Daokou, community prevention and control, and orderly resumption of work. As of February 14, the city's nine interprovincial highway crossings, 20 public security checkpoints on the ground, and 63 other outer crossings, more than 2.43 million vehicles and 5.6 million personnel were examined, 1,676 people were sent to the central isolation observation point, 587 people with abnormal body temperature were transferred, and 4,854 vehicles and 8,220 people were urged to return to Shanghai. In addition to land routes, railways, airports and other channels into Shanghai are also the focus of the investigation. At airports and train stations, each arriving passenger is required to undergo a temperature check and information registration verification.

The information registration of the personnel returning to Shanghai from Daokou is the first step, and the real management is ultimately to be implemented to the grass-roots level on the fine prevention and control, it can be said that the real battlefield or grass-roots level. Xie Hua also mentioned in an interview with the media, "The objectives and means of the epidemic prevention work are very clear, the goal is to reduce transmission, and the means is to cut off the transmission route. The online registration system is just a way to identify people who need to be focused, and to really find and manage them, it's up to the grassroots and the community."
